dcterms:description: The Oregon State Design Repository (OSDR) is a structured taxonomy-based data source that houses product lifecycle inventory data along with assigned specialized taxonomy descriptions, including product assembly child-parent notation and functional-flow basis assignment to components.
dcterms:title: Oregon State Design Repository (OSDR)

dcterms:title: Oregon State Design Repository (OSDR) (Subset used in the work)

dcterms:description: Assembly graphs representing the data from the Oregon State Design Repository (OSDR), capturing function-flow-assembly relationships within products.
